  {
    "user": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1737578939.937709",
    "client_msg_id": "8d2f68e8-2f5e-47b0-91fd-0745bd9c6ff2",
    "text": "Yes Josh, that's precisely the good shit I came here for! Full size!\n\nI've heard people say \"rules should be defined in the same place they're executed\", but I don't think I've seen anyone do it yet. Like, <@U03R0B9U1GD> talked about something this with respect to <https://www.todepond.com/explore/cellpond/|CellPond>, for insty. Rather than paddles down the left of the screen, you'd… uh… not have them there.\n\nI'm not sure about CA rules, but simple replacement rules seem do-able, perhaps. Maybe a pair of brushes that let you capture a \"before\" and \"after\" that recognize some changing qualities of the captured sand, and a brush to apply that change.\n\nI wonder if there's something about little grains of sand that might make this all more feasible. Sand is basically 1-bit graphics without the pixel grid. It's like the _second_ most constrained kind of graphics possible, surely.\n\nMaybe some <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9G0r7jL3xl8|Viewpoint> vibes here.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1737568493.612189",
    "parent_user_id": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "mrEBs",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Yes Josh, that's precisely the good shit I came here for! Full size!\n\nI've heard people say \"rules should be defined in the same place they're executed\", but I don't think I've seen anyone do it yet. Like, "
              },
              {
                "type": "user",
                "user_id": "U03R0B9U1GD"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " talked about something this with respect to "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://www.todepond.com/explore/cellpond/",
                "text": "CellPond"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", for insty. Rather than paddles down the left of the screen, you'd… uh… not have them there.\n\nI'm not sure about CA rules, but simple replacement rules seem do-able, perhaps. Maybe a pair of brushes that let you capture a \"before\" and \"after\" that recognize some changing qualities of the captured sand, and a brush to apply that change.\n\nI wonder if there's something about little grains of sand that might make this all more feasible. Sand is basically 1-bit graphics without the pixel grid. It's like the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "second",
                "style": {
                  "italic": true
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " most constrained kind of graphics possible, surely.\n\nMaybe some "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9G0r7jL3xl8",
                "text": "Viewpoint"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " vibes here."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "reactions": [
      {
        "name": "heart",
        "users": [
          "U05M5A8E0NT"
        ],
        "count": 1
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "devlog-together",
    "channel_id": "C03RR0W5DGC"
  },
